      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i was reading something though about how some people say the whole movement was mostly just about those big nonviolent protests and the big leaders, and that it doesn't really account for how much more radical groups or even different political strategies helped push things along. like, was the nonviolent approach the only way it worked or was that just the version of history we're taught?",
