      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The narrative focusing solely on nonviolent protest and major leaders is a highly sanitized version of history. While nonviolence was incredibly effective in gaining moral ground and legislative wins, the movement was fueled by a diverse spectrum of tactics. More radical elements and grassroots organizing were essential in applying pressure and pushing the boundaries of acceptable change. To ignore these varied strategies is to present an incomplete and politically convenient picture.",
